values:
Eventually got in contact with Mike, when he came online earlier, and we're still meeting up. Albeit it's a bit earlier than we arranged (10.00am!) but I haven't seen him since July last year so I hope have a great day! Of course we speak online whenever we can, but we haven't really sat down and had a laugh and a chat for ages!

He's going to let me drag him around town for the day, and in return, he's going to buy me lunch, just like he used to do when we were at college!

Things I'm hoping to buy:

  • The three set collection of Doctor Who books, from W H Smith (Sad I know, but they really need to be on my bookshelf!)
  • A pair of shoes for Friday evening (Now I have money, I can get a nice pair)
  • Some clothes for Friday evening (Ditto the above!)
  • Some make up

Ah yes, Friday evening, I'm off out on a girly night out with a few mates of mine. Meeting at my main friend's mum's flat, having a few drinkies, then off down to the Social Club, staying there till 10.20ish then off down to Bogey's for about 10.30 cuz so we can get in free!

Things to take with me on Friday:

  • Make up
  • Clothes for Bogey's
  • Clothes for the next day
  • Night clothes (as I'm staying at the flat)
  • Make up removers
  • Toothbrush / paste
  • Straighteners(?)
  • Passport! (Absolutley essential - as I still don't look old enough to drink!, Yet alone get in to clubs)
  • Money
  • Mobile Phone

Full of this stupid cold still! I've put some Obus Oil on a tissue to help me breathe a bit better, and now my nose is full of gunk. I've been asked if I want to go out on Friday night, and stay at my mate Cassie's mum's flat for the night. Seeing as I don't have work the next the day, I've said I will go, as long as I have the time I need to get down to the flat etc. Plus I hope this cold has gone by then.

Currently trying to:

a) Get in touch with mate Mike, as we're supposed to be meeting up tomorrow afternoon

b) Concentrate on writing this, and not dancing to Madonna

c) Sort out money for tomorrow and Friday

Phrase of the day: I'm ill

Song of the day: Can't Get You Out Of My Bed... Sorry Head - Kylie Minogue

Slow and Steady
Your friends see you as painstaking and fussy.

They see you as very cautious, extremely careful, a slow and steady plodder.

It'd really surprise them if you ever did something impulsively or on the spur of the moment.

They expect you to examine everything carefully from every angle and then usually decide against it.

Your Blog Should Be Purple

You tend to set blogging trends, and you're the most likely to write your own meme or survey.
You are a bit distant though. Your blog is all about you - not what anyone else has to say.

Your Life Path Number is 3

You are a creative and artistic person with an interesting view on life.

A total social butterfly, you're the life of any party.

In love, you inspire and enchant your partner. You are often an object of fantasy and desire.

While you are very talented, you sometimes lack the ambition to put your talents in play.
And while your wit carries you a long way, you occasionally use it to mask your true feelings.
Your natural abilities can bring you all the success in the world ... if you let them

After a big talk with my dad about how going to bed early, going for a walk every so often can do you good, I took up his offer and went for a walk by myself this afternoon. I left the house about 20 past 3 and got home about 10 past 4. I took my mobile phone, some tissues,(as I have picked up yet another cold from work!) some money and my MP3 player and just walked for ages, until I did a full circle!

  • Proverb of the day: Sad people never walk fast
  • Song of the day: Good Riddance (Time of Your Life) - Green Day
